        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 4:24PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 424 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm
capable of producing a landspout over San Luis Valley Airport, moving
east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Landspouts, wind gusts up to 50 mph, and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible. Gusty winds
could knock down tree limbs and blow around unsecured
objects.

Locations impacted include...
Alamosa, San Luis Valley Airport, and Alamosa East.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
